<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 3:45PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT
SOUTHEASTERN SMYTH...SOUTHWESTERN WYTHE AND CENTRAL GRAYSON COUNTIES
THROUGH 415 PM EDT...
At 345 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Troutdale, or over Sugar Grove, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Rural Retreat...
Sugar Grove...
Mount Rogers National Recreation Area...
Speedwell...
Troutdale...
Marion Wytheville...
and Atkins.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
